HEADWORD: Stuck-up
<hw>Stuck"-up`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Self-important and
supercilious, conceited; vain; arrogant.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The airs of small, <qex>stuck-up</qex>, men.</q> <rj><qau>A. K. H.
Boyd.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

